<body>
    <h1>Bitloops Layered Extension Architecture: Why It Is Needed and How I=
t Should Look</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"f4c449d07cd7" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchite=
cture:WhyItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture"=
>Bitloops Layered Extension Architecture</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"504f8eef20d7" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Purpose">Purpose</h2>
<p local-id=3D"5adccc860a42">This document defines the <strong>layered exte=
nsion architecture</strong> Bitloops should adopt across the product.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ee34a72b40f1">The goal is to establish a broader extension m=
odel that explains:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"9713a6788073">
<li local-id=3D"1ad270ff15d2">
<p local-id=3D"6fea8d175fd1">why Bitloops needs multiple extension seams ra=
ther than one generic plugin mechanism</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c735f9d0188e">
<p local-id=3D"9f0316bcf2a5">which parts of the system should remain Core</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e81b8d362b10">
<p local-id=3D"3930e0b4dd46">which parts should be extensible</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b191bd3fa748">
<p local-id=3D"3d326bae48e4">how those extension layers should interact</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"248921a5b604">
<p local-id=3D"26458d8c4f07">how this architecture supports product reach, =
platform velocity, security, and monetisation</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"6d53c375c0ef">This is the <strong>umbrella architecture docu=
ment</strong> for the topic.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b07ab0bc4832">Follow-up documents should deep dive into each=
 category separately.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"5eb543816926">
<h2 local-id=3D"37d07d344e0d" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-ExecutiveSummary">Executive Summary</h2>
<p local-id=3D"88aa67db2ebd">Bitloops is now reaching the point where a sin=
gle monolithic architecture is no longer the right shape.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3f6b4fefcfcd">The pressure is coming from multiple direction=
s at once:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c6b199c693bb">
<li local-id=3D"8581b2a99fe6">
<p local-id=3D"7ae1685ffde6">DevQL capabilities are diverging in complexity=
 and rate of change</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e483a77e270b">
<p local-id=3D"258a8f85dc87">agent support is expanding across multiple env=
ironments and protocols</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a7e6dfb14826">
<p local-id=3D"720859f37552">language support must grow far beyond Rust and=
 TypeScript</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"81b07cfc1fa1">
<p local-id=3D"3d9c0ee5b4ee">model/inference backends need to remain flexib=
le</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3bf6b98d005d">
<p local-id=3D"8774f1957c5a">connectors and test/coverage ecosystems are br=
oadening</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"640c4aefe6fd">
<p local-id=3D"b119eba2ef6d">dashboard and remote API/server concerns are e=
merging</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b118e18786e8">
<p local-id=3D"4daf2efce661">enterprise and paid product requirements intro=
duce stronger security, governance, and deployment needs</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1bd4b77a996f">These pressures cannot be served by a monolith=
ic architecture and should not all be solved by a single generic =E2=80=9Cp=
lugin system=E2=80=9D either.</p>
<p local-id=3D"be17304f0317">Instead, Bitloops should adopt a <strong>layer=
ed extension architecture</strong> with clear categories of extensibility.<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"1563f68397c2">The proposed model has four layers:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2f80656f42a0">
<li local-id=3D"669285d74bc3">
<p local-id=3D"5d178b7f02be"><strong>Capability Packs</strong> <br>
User-visible intelligence extensions such as Knowledge, Semantic Clones, an=
d Test Harness.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8d1adab9aaa6">
<p local-id=3D"f3ec86326025"><strong>Adapter Plugins</strong> <br>
Integration seams such as agent adapters, language packs, model providers, =
connectors, coverage adapters, and auth providers.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4c1c3b25322d">
<p local-id=3D"f8f9805b56da"><strong>Runtime Products</strong> <br>
Different deployment shapes built on shared open-core foundations, includin=
g local CLI and remote server products.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9bc171dc4e11">
<p local-id=3D"26054fbf1c41"><strong>Commercial / Governance Packs</strong>=
 <br>
Paid or enterprise-oriented layers such as private inference, internal conn=
ectors, remote shared services, policy, audit, and governance.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"6113e79ac390">This architecture is needed because Bitloops i=
s no longer just a local CLI with a query layer.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9ba58ede60d3">It is already becoming a platform.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"0d685331b855">
<h2 local-id=3D"1ff5d1372772" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-TheProblemWeAreActuallySolving">The Problem W=
e Are Actually Solving</h2>
<p local-id=3D"1baa2a0e5821">There are several extension pressures currentl=
y appearing at the same time.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"0800cf1a0217" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-1.DevQLcapabilitiesarediverging">1. DevQL cap=
abilities are diverging</h3>
<p local-id=3D"74904bf5b83e">Knowledge, Semantic Clones, Test Harness, and =
future capabilities do not evolve at the same speed and do not share the sa=
me dependencies.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"45a1075a3dc8" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-2.Agentsupportisexpanding">2. Agent support i=
s expanding</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4e6e56c941b3">Right now, support for different agents can ea=
sily become hardcoded.</p>
<p local-id=3D"544cb6ab0ef1">But different agent environments introduce rea=
l variation:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"664932d1032e">
<li local-id=3D"58ff6fa9911b">
<p local-id=3D"c9e66b730906">transport/protocol expectations</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"70953d625e90">
<p local-id=3D"abecdb0e6bc8">tool discovery shape</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ca1921215dd4">
<p local-id=3D"3471df8c77dd">instruction surface</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8a3490cde72e">
<p local-id=3D"9cf14bc03d8f">session lifecycle</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3e0be11d2f17">
<p local-id=3D"8a333e079057">auth/bootstrap expectations</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"824502f47655">
<p local-id=3D"900782e07bc4">limitations of each ecosystem</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"436f5035f2b0">If these differences are hardcoded into the pr=
oduct, the host will become cluttered and brittle.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"b51fd7df2caf" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-3.Languagesupportmustscale">3. Language suppo=
rt must scale</h3>
<p local-id=3D"05c62a6a21be">Bitloops cannot remain limited to Rust and Typ=
eScript.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f9b4ac1a7133">Adding new languages should not require scatte=
ring language-specific logic across Core.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0d4b9b18e706">The platform needs a consistent way to add:</p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"e373a1a69b6c">
<li local-id=3D"15bc5ace28b3">
<p local-id=3D"08656ed65719">parsers</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"456934117c72">
<p local-id=3D"db9505a2d522">artefact extraction rules</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e6e0fb5bd236">
<p local-id=3D"621e4a42b3a6">symbol and dependency rules</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"65273ad5846e">
<p local-id=3D"0cbfb704a543">test discovery conventions</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"802c1f4a1806">
<p local-id=3D"5d4b6e0c1900">language-specific capability enrichments</p></=
li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"6aaaf5eb9fa9" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-4.Deploymentshapeischanging">4. Deployment sh=
ape is changing</h3>
<p local-id=3D"adff80cfef64">Bitloops is not only a local CLI anymore.</p>
<p local-id=3D"041a90f76713">The product direction now includes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"635a4247395e">
<li local-id=3D"06e1fe45c6f3">
<p local-id=3D"671cee190ba0">dashboard/API surfaces</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0e71ca669754">
<p local-id=3D"771094b637c8">remote shared services</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"abdd89c06d3d">
<p local-id=3D"1c3031ebe0c7">security and shared database concerns</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0c336b7a5ac9">
<p local-id=3D"c6ccdeb7480b">remote CLI/agent access to a common backend</p=
></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c60c885f72e7">That means Bitloops is moving from a <strong>s=
ingle local runtime</strong> toward <strong>multiple runtimes</strong> buil=
t on shared foundations.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"8fa61a6c6672" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-5.Productandmonetisationconcernsareincreasing=
">5. Product and monetisation concerns are increasing</h3>
<p local-id=3D"b7f5eaad8a86">Some extensions are not merely technical.</p>
<p local-id=3D"287761fc75bd">They are commercial and operational boundaries=
:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"0efe236f0f05">
<li local-id=3D"77d57ad88d8f">
<p local-id=3D"fbc353fadc2a">private model routing</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2af8326b1c24">
<p local-id=3D"76312ca38649">internal enterprise connectors</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"803a0445be68">
<p local-id=3D"90d325552e8d">auditability</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8af1ea661275">
<p local-id=3D"88a9536bf26d">policy enforcement</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a03c61d6779">
<p local-id=3D"4f13073535c2">remote shared services</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7b8eb93f5bd8">
<p local-id=3D"3f7b818d4d01">governance and entitlements</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"22178bfb12db">These should not be mixed conceptually with or=
dinary language or provider adapters.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"491a08adc153">
<h2 local-id=3D"8143210bc4c6" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-WhyOneGenericPluginSystemIsNotEnough">Why One=
 Generic Plugin System Is Not Enough</h2>
<p local-id=3D"8fa08e1093bb">A single undifferentiated plugin model would c=
reate confusion and bad boundaries.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0e327b5a7210">For example:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"59a8d08d1579">
<li local-id=3D"64200ac9c19d">
<p local-id=3D"84f499587513">a Knowledge capability is not the same kind of=
 thing as a Python language pack</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"18489aa973f6">
<p local-id=3D"2608d54d99f5">a Claude Code adapter is not the same kind of =
thing as an enterprise compliance module</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"835ff0daee05">
<p local-id=3D"779005fdc286">a remote multi-user server runtime is not the =
same kind of thing as a DevQL stage extension</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"58e7f532a0ca">They differ in:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"aa8d52befd27">
<li local-id=3D"ef4407a9ac8c">
<p local-id=3D"0d8ca4a6c2b3">lifecycle</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8bc7b55ca597">
<p local-id=3D"4aa2bd9ae0d1">risk profile</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"52560d97b684">
<p local-id=3D"c500fddf8e7a">ownership</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"411543524853">
<p local-id=3D"6cf41f91d45b">testing model</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"146426452a43">
<p local-id=3D"71fc4abdd331">security implications</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2e9f06e84293">
<p local-id=3D"9c689b7660d0">packaging implications</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4b2d62fc32d0">
<p local-id=3D"f890a79028b2">monetisation role</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f62d8b29849e">If all of these are treated as the same catego=
ry of plugin, Bitloops will lose architectural clarity.</p>
<p local-id=3D"45659f9686d2">So the correct move is not:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"f8ff005c1619">
<p local-id=3D"911bd88dbee8">=E2=80=9CLet=E2=80=99s make everything a plugi=
n.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"4d0981b8d884">The correct move is:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"bca7b218f22e">
<p local-id=3D"4b926911ba4f">=E2=80=9CLet=E2=80=99s define the right extens=
ion seam for each category of change.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"f502b0a7379d">
<h2 local-id=3D"35bd32ce298a" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-ArchitecturePrinciples">Architecture Principl=
es</h2>
<p local-id=3D"e7262a7b7965">The layered extension architecture should foll=
ow these principles.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"089c3f3d9a01" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-1.KeepCoresmall,stable,andopinionated">1. Kee=
p Core small, stable, and opinionated</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f83319ae29cf">Core should own the platform foundations that =
must remain coherent across every extension type.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"9f74f03c2a5b" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-2.Differentkindsofextensibilityshouldusediffe=
rentcontracts">2. Different kinds of extensibility should use different con=
tracts</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d662e94f80f0">Capability packs, language packs, agent adapte=
rs, and runtimes are not the same thing and should not share a fake one-siz=
e-fits-all abstraction.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d514383973c4" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-3.User-visiblevalueshouldmaptocleanproductsur=
faces">3. User-visible value should map to clean product surfaces</h3>
<p local-id=3D"df3b2be04908">Top-level packaging boundaries should correspo=
nd to things users understand and buy, not low-level implementation details=
.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"1a79c98de57f" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-4.Extensionsshouldbeadditive,notdestabilising=
">4. Extensions should be additive, not destabilising</h3>
<p local-id=3D"2242555bee88">New extensions should expand Bitloops without =
repeatedly forcing redesign of the host.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"8d2f79af559a" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-5.Security,provenance,andpolicystayhost-contr=
olled">5. Security, provenance, and policy stay host-controlled</h3>
<p local-id=3D"7d5ac16b3972">Extension does not mean unrestricted execution=
 or ad hoc data access.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"30c59dd67c97" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-6.Open-corereuseshouldbemaximisedacrossruntim=
es">6. Open-core reuse should be maximised across runtimes</h3>
<p local-id=3D"daceebe06cbd">Local CLI and remote/server products should sh=
are core libraries and canonical models wherever possible.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"df92c0b3aece" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-7.Paid/enterprisevalueshouldhaveexplicitbound=
aries">7. Paid/enterprise value should have explicit boundaries</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ca1353767f8d">Commercial layers should not be accidental by-=
products of the codebase. They should be recognised as first-class product =
architecture concerns.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"3cbd45e0d069">
<h2 local-id=3D"459cce87f694" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-TheProposedLayeredModel">The Proposed Layered=
 Model</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">flowcha=
rt TD
    A["Core Platform"] --&gt; B["Capability Packs"]
    A --&gt; C["Adapter Plugins"]
    A --&gt; D["Runtime Products"]
    A --&gt; E["Commercial / Governance Packs"]

    subgraph sg1 [" "]
        B1["Knowledge"]
        B2["Semantic Clones"]
        B3["Test Harness"]
    end
    B --&gt; sg1

    subgraph sg2 [" "]
        C1["Agent Adapters"]
        C2["Language Packs"]
        C3["Model Providers"]
        C4["Connectors"]
        C5["Coverage/Test Adapters"]
        C6["Auth / Storage Adapters"]
    end
    C --&gt; sg2

    subgraph sg3 [" "]
        D1["Local CLI Runtime"]
        D2["Remote Server Runtime"]
        D3["Dashboard/API Runtime"]
    end
    D --&gt; sg3

    subgraph sg4 [" "]
        E1["Private Inference"]
        E2["Internal Connectors"]
        E3["Policy / Compliance"]
        E4["Governance / Audit"]
    end
    E --&gt; sg4</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"875c6e28b6dd">
<h2 local-id=3D"90b9cc4b777c" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Layer1:CapabilityPacks"><a href=3D"https://bi=
tloops.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADCP/pages/452591621/DevQL+Capability+Pack=
s+Architecture+and+Implementation+Compass" data-linked-resource-id=3D"45259=
1621" data-linked-resource-version=3D"8" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page"=
>Layer 1: Capability Packs</a></h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"b0906ead53dc" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Definition">Definition</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a1f0f90975f4">Capability packs are <strong>user-visible inte=
lligence extensions</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7cdcb3febf08">They add meaningful behaviour to Bitloops=E2=
=80=99 reasoning, retrieval, or analysis surface.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d319f2c8fee1">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6766ebdc8e97">
<li local-id=3D"4da77a0a2ed6">
<p local-id=3D"05f39e67ea63">Knowledge</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"23c3c7080d8a">
<p local-id=3D"8ff3dba10414">Semantic Clones</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bee8e988d8e4">
<p local-id=3D"0a73debf5ced">Test Harness</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a198138a5d12">
<p local-id=3D"c079e0d8a754">future compliance/evidence or workflow reasoni=
ng packs</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"e1d875c2d67d" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Whattheyshouldown">What they should own</h3>
<p local-id=3D"aeafb25797a0">Capability packs may contribute:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c0f9ca5e3ead">
<li local-id=3D"67871a8def79">
<p local-id=3D"b9059e69ba41">query stages and higher-level DevQL surfaces</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8bd693d0b6e3">
<p local-id=3D"6bdc2277c745">ingestion hooks or enrichers specific to the c=
apability</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e243b162563c">
<p local-id=3D"cbd9fc6c24ac">capability-specific scoring, ranking, or infer=
ence logic</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eea99cdf6f0a">
<p local-id=3D"2029635e597c">schema/discoverability metadata</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"15e3aeb3ff39">
<p local-id=3D"d2183ac0b5df">capability-owned migrations through host APIs<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"9076543de273" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Whattheyshouldnotown">What they should not ow=
n</h3>
<p local-id=3D"e351f2a9f948">Capability packs should not own:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3444333dee9c">
<li local-id=3D"4c74605cf4d5">
<p local-id=3D"5bd338d60ade">canonical repo/temporal semantics</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"48727a2b7089">
<p local-id=3D"fb53122a64a2">unrestricted storage access</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"41b339ffdc67">
<p local-id=3D"d5f827d35672">global policy enforcement</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"100d1b92a524">
<p local-id=3D"754450e5188e">host-owned provenance rules</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"90f8177ba9df">
<p local-id=3D"ffe7dd95cb22">runtime-specific security policy</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"1484eafaaec4" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Whythiscategoryexists">Why this category exis=
ts</h3>
<p local-id=3D"076a2c108e74">These are the highest-value product extensions=
.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f8bad6757c88">They are the main engine of user-facing intell=
igence, packaging, and differentiated value.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"b615b99bb3b4">
<h2 local-id=3D"bb57bf540d4c" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Layer2:AdapterPlugins">Layer 2: Adapter Plugi=
ns</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"a17f01d2771c" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Definition.1">Definition</h3>
<p local-id=3D"3293ba35a642">Adapter plugins are <strong>integration seams<=
/strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7c17c2d8610b">They do not primarily define new product capab=
ilities.</p>
<p local-id=3D"8c2493960d42">Instead, they let Bitloops operate across diff=
erent ecosystems, protocols, providers, and technical environments.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"f019cadc9b8b" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Mainsubcategories">Main subcategories</h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"2a71fb29044a" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-A.AgentAdapters">A. Agent Adapters</h4>
<p local-id=3D"9250dd103c3d">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6c7719d94ae4">
<li local-id=3D"4b185dd1fa93">
<p local-id=3D"fcedf1e90db3">Claude Code</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"045529c8b8e5">
<p local-id=3D"77773c421c9c">Codex</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"daeae7991819">
<p local-id=3D"03b8d6151f61">Cursor</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"549d2fc92cee">
<p local-id=3D"79180429eba4">Gemini</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a00d03516006">
<p local-id=3D"a959f5a41c5f">Copilot</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9338520fbcc2">
<p local-id=3D"7732dd3ad8cd">generic MCP-compatible adapters</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"13fa1ad7188e">These should translate between Bitloops=E2=80=
=99 internal agent-facing contract and the quirks of each agent environment=
.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"8bd3c310f0da" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-B.LanguagePacks">B. Language Packs</h4>
<p local-id=3D"df84b9e56202">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3c8f42322fed">
<li local-id=3D"3c14e3edea58">
<p local-id=3D"5e3c5deb7ab0">Rust</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9b7f94cf0921">
<p local-id=3D"156d9641717d">TypeScript</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"847f71417fa6">
<p local-id=3D"c246083c8a9e">Python</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4c90f282f83b">
<p local-id=3D"3c8389267107">Java</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e0b81002cd2e">
<p local-id=3D"f9467b1df47c">Go</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"39f5caa3c384">
<p local-id=3D"bf9dba41ea01">C#</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"47898ed67ed8">These should contribute language-specific supp=
ort such as parsing, artefact extraction, symbol modeling, test discovery c=
onventions, and language-aware enrichments.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"27b90f0703e5" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-C.Model/InferenceProviders">C. Model / Infere=
nce Providers</h4>
<p local-id=3D"f25f6eb0739b">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c068f32b7363">
<li local-id=3D"ced51c43b1c7">
<p local-id=3D"e300efca92fd">OpenAI</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0e8f5ec04ff9">
<p local-id=3D"e1d721648e72">Anthropic</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a535c8eae699">
<p local-id=3D"f52ed2c517e2">Voyage</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"95256ff311ac">
<p local-id=3D"8282b3b8d645">Ollama</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8108a4b3cce5">
<p local-id=3D"56715ae83e43">local embedding backends</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"66b64b43ee96">
<p local-id=3D"5a37a70cd2e9">enterprise private model gateways</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"3e2a6aee7978" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-D.ConnectorProviders">D. Connector Providers<=
/h4>
<p local-id=3D"02f31407ce55">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"130daced52fd">
<li local-id=3D"2c81faed8c5b">
<p local-id=3D"d5de26e80c9a">GitHub</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"07ae962289fe">
<p local-id=3D"46fdcfd35ba0">GitLab</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bd82e11574d0">
<p local-id=3D"72d6ddc4fe20">Bitbucket</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f7f229766e92">
<p local-id=3D"72b2b0a4c4e2">Jira</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c86dafb408dd">
<p local-id=3D"f674877ea25d">Confluence</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1905a294cc4c">
<p local-id=3D"dfc99cde3cd3">Linear</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3012bcd9b5d4">
<p local-id=3D"299f7b03d2f9">Notion</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f3e8a630892b">
<p local-id=3D"d8c43b2d380f">internal systems</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"fac27ef6670f" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-E.Test/CoverageAdapters"><span class=3D"inlin=
e-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"512366e0-d7b0-43d3-959b-211154c44dbb">E. Test=
 / Coverage Adapters</span></h4>
<p local-id=3D"3f55342068b3">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7b873e1d2f0e">
<li local-id=3D"283019e1c2c4">
<p local-id=3D"e5adfde7ca59">LCOV</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fc8182fc1dcb">
<p local-id=3D"9a53654ff2cc">JaCoCo</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ccff5fc32f38">
<p local-id=3D"4ef29a8f7132">Cobertura</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c997410432ec">
<p local-id=3D"da6d7c152bd0">language/framework-specific coverage providers=
</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"7737e12a4459" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-F.Othertechnicaladapters">F. Other technical =
adapters</h4>
<p local-id=3D"3dded9c7d19f">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bdd4853807b1">
<li local-id=3D"8fd8ca25c842">
<p local-id=3D"6ea55a71f28e">auth provider adapters</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fdb39dd39938">
<p local-id=3D"21fac5aef32d">vector backend adapters</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"33d6eb7d2013">
<p local-id=3D"587b8c249fe4">storage provider adapters where appropriate</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"5dba216fd6a3" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Whythiscategoryexists.1">Why this category ex=
ists</h3>
<p local-id=3D"be0137d95304">Without adapter seams, Bitloops will either:</=
p>
<ul local-id=3D"92958bab1952">
<li local-id=3D"3de85a432460">
<p local-id=3D"220b6f08df9b">hardcode ecosystem-specific logic into the hos=
t, or</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5d03039adf96">
<p local-id=3D"f1d0e182177d">block future growth by making every new integr=
ation feel like a core rewrite</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"fa54ca4b1352">Adapter plugins are the main way Bitloops can =
broaden reach without destroying host clarity.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"c83758f6218f">
<h2 local-id=3D"814b5c0f67a2" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Layer3:RuntimeProducts">Layer 3: Runtime Prod=
ucts</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"c48210a45b5e" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Definition.2">Definition</h3>
<p local-id=3D"2da87c31256f">Runtime products are <strong>different deploym=
ent and consumption shapes</strong> built on shared open-core foundations.<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"84232f03b8fb">This is not just =E2=80=9Canother plugin type.=
=E2=80=9D</p>
<p local-id=3D"fccc29a94b55">A runtime changes how Bitloops is executed, se=
cured, exposed, and operated.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"4ddc87fc8203" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Mainruntimeshapes">Main runtime shapes</h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"4c1e8ec10043" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-A.LocalCLIRuntime">A. Local CLI Runtime</h4>
<p local-id=3D"b658538cd87d">The local-first developer runtime.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"e5ef3d05a46b" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-B.RemoteServerRuntime">B. Remote Server Runti=
me</h4>
<p local-id=3D"55b926aefc21">A shared or hosted runtime that can expose API=
s to remote CLI agents or team environments, backed by a shared DB and stro=
nger security controls.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"feeb9a622bdc" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-C.Dashboard/APIRuntime">C. Dashboard / API Ru=
ntime</h4>
<p local-id=3D"eb6c059d81ad">A product/runtime surface supporting UI, API, =
admin, and broader operational interactions.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"6183b5c6c6ce" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Whyruntimeshouldbeitsowncategory">Why runtime=
 should be its own category</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6280f0a3f6c2">A remote server product introduces concerns th=
at are qualitatively different from local plugin extension:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"9da9b6292e60">
<li local-id=3D"527c9e8063cd">
<p local-id=3D"f58b0c88a22f">authn/authz</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"34b871ae3f90">
<p local-id=3D"74979fdcaf0f">tenancy</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4d8754158d13">
<p local-id=3D"5094b397598e">secrets handling</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fadb01435a5b">
<p local-id=3D"4e9659acd2ee">job execution</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ac7f572ed77f">
<p local-id=3D"38c66ddf5b1f">request isolation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"85dc303379d6">
<p local-id=3D"efe42c1a4510">quotas and rate limiting</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f8fe357776f2">
<p local-id=3D"c5e8d4b6150c">auditability</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"08742ac430e5">
<p local-id=3D"a93358e2e796">shared DB security</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ebe0047857ba">
<p local-id=3D"6ecd3389fa11">org-level policy enforcement</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a48aae8ec81f">
<p local-id=3D"f9a6e8301f48">service operations</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"9e910d745e91">This means the right model is generally:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"16dd02f10345">
<li local-id=3D"6dd0fb44fb5a">
<p local-id=3D"af0356f1ebd3">shared open-core crates and contracts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7a7363f34ec8">
<p local-id=3D"d480019068ce">multiple runtimes built on those foundations</=
p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c227ca90cc0f">not:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c3e34d33b131">
<li local-id=3D"4fed3c658bf6">
<p local-id=3D"35df225b1197">=E2=80=9Cbolt a server onto the CLI via one pl=
ugin=E2=80=9D</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"3ad8a47aa970" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Recommendeddirection">Recommended direction</=
h3>
<p local-id=3D"795f61ab7f6c">The server product should most likely be a <st=
rong>separate runtime/product</strong> built on shared open-core crates, ra=
ther than a thin extension of the local CLI executable.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"c2098f26408f">
<h2 local-id=3D"1f38bf076f74" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Layer4:Commercial/GovernancePacks">Layer 4: C=
ommercial / Governance Packs</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"4575eb3802bc" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Definition.3">Definition</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ea0be1d18adb">Commercial / governance packs are <strong>paid=
, enterprise-oriented, or operationally sensitive layers</strong> that buil=
d on the rest of the platform.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b451202ce9a4">Examples:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b5fcd7603e0c">
<li local-id=3D"d30aa2a6b525">
<p local-id=3D"0dc8cfb0001f">private model routing</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b4bd66accbe2">
<p local-id=3D"07c059830489">internal enterprise connectors</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"912f6aaa1508">
<p local-id=3D"bef81d1db351">policy engines</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2cf69cf4cef6">
<p local-id=3D"19312355faef">compliance evidence generation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"789b25fb28a4">
<p local-id=3D"a02b837a6a5a">audit logging and governance controls</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"894de42bc905">
<p local-id=3D"9ec5b6bfca36">remote shared service features</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"acbdb28b2e30">
<p local-id=3D"e8e8349220bf">org-level controls and entitlements</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"8a74d666f4b1" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Whythiscategoryexists.2">Why this category ex=
ists</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f04d53507c2c">These concerns are not just technical extensio=
n seams.</p>
<p local-id=3D"99afda38e1ec">They are product, trust, and revenue boundarie=
s.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2629ec6611b8">Making them explicit helps Bitloops:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b9eb883d5583">
<li local-id=3D"0b3855000514">
<p local-id=3D"211da1c106a4">avoid accidental product sprawl</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"951d7d23c5d7">
<p local-id=3D"b0a6ba0a32ca">define cleaner paid tiers</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f052fe006353">
<p local-id=3D"ed52c8ae86be">keep enterprise/security concerns first-class =
rather than bolted on later</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"67d7b47459e5">
<h2 local-id=3D"6b645a7a4c34" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-WhatMustStayCore">What Must Stay Core</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f68cc73cc9f8">A layered extension architecture only works if=
 the right things remain firmly inside Core.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5fcf74449e16">Core should own:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6d002cae8b3a">
<li local-id=3D"d89bf7d7b427">
<p local-id=3D"59a22c1dcfa7">canonical artefact model</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9f8c1258294b">
<p local-id=3D"b4ba82ac2d3a">temporal semantics and commit-addressable trut=
h</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d86fec13a42f">
<p local-id=3D"04fd84b1a960">provenance model</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e1ccda006fe0">
<p local-id=3D"3702d1bc80a2">query kernel</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cdafc520f452">
<p local-id=3D"ef2ba800fabc">capability and adapter registry mechanisms</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"412d139ed304">
<p local-id=3D"bb8a3283304b">extension API/versioning discipline</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"228f2f6014cc">
<p local-id=3D"3d2c71ff23bc">migration orchestration</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4e6b2b076800">
<p local-id=3D"4f1d00ca58ec">tenancy/security policy foundations</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"43bfc2f06092">
<p local-id=3D"c2d3dcd11480">entitlement enforcement</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6a6595affd8c">
<p local-id=3D"9f1e9d9b2135">host-side validation and safety rules</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"a2eb98fc3fd9">These are not good plugin candidates.</p>
<p local-id=3D"402a7d452fb6">If they become extension-owned too early, Bitl=
oops will lose coherence.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"1556aa5be5f2">
<h2 local-id=3D"2c34c024e986" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-OpenCoreandProductBoundary">Open Core and Pro=
duct Boundary</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f3f13f6e6706">The architecture strongly suggests an <strong>=
open-core foundation with multiple product layers built on top</strong>.</p=
>
<p local-id=3D"365de5e8c957">A reasonable split is:</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"765e4af5efbc" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Sharedopen-corefoundations">Shared open-core =
foundations</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"1eaaa95896c6">
<li local-id=3D"f8520ca09d1a">
<p local-id=3D"efb3cc8a2682">artefact graph</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"000c57079d1b">
<p local-id=3D"ac67daa65d5d">temporal model</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3e81a95ed613">
<p local-id=3D"7abba303fb76">query engine</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b7c04fef9181">
<p local-id=3D"214f29f99c68">extension registries and contracts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bda66d277f95">
<p local-id=3D"bb0a42920e9c">base store abstractions</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"77c5bc1ae18b">
<p local-id=3D"484387ed6f40">capability execution foundations</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cafbd00caf44">
<p local-id=3D"16da9d2845e8">common provider and runtime abstractions</p></=
li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"79a59ac5e0ff" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Product/runtimelayersbuiltontop">Product/runt=
ime layers built on top</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"76117fc1da75">
<li local-id=3D"66b8f9d211a4">
<p local-id=3D"a323345fb45b">local CLI product</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e6c43f2ab8e9">
<p local-id=3D"80b11d09d319">remote server product</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8959bc40bd65">
<p local-id=3D"48babf09752c">dashboard/API product</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"82e4c23ec71b">
<p local-id=3D"f5852ebec074">enterprise/commercial packs</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2482339d37a7">This gives Bitloops:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"e0acc17020f6">
<li local-id=3D"846b4b7f25de">
<p local-id=3D"63534aacdf95">reuse across runtimes</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b4b5c55432a9">
<p local-id=3D"e65941614fa3">consistency across local and remote products</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"727cd4e8feaf">
<p local-id=3D"0525a243d0e0">a cleaner monetisation story</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3893ee3a9f33">
<p local-id=3D"b57007b7c3b0">less pressure to twist the CLI into every futu=
re deployment shape</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"b2aed7a2cc14">
<h2 local-id=3D"05a20f1dbcc3" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-HowTheLayersInteract">How The Layers Interact=
</h2>
<p local-id=3D"11c22a51b4f1">The intended interaction model is:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2da027124511">
<li local-id=3D"0a22c25f8a9e">
<p local-id=3D"4a167a1fe136"><strong>Core</strong> provides the canonical m=
odel and extension contracts.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6748ae59e226">
<p local-id=3D"defa2769bcf8"><strong>Adapter plugins</strong> expand the ec=
osystems Bitloops can operate in.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7b55b3b0e512">
<p local-id=3D"1840e2635549"><strong>Capability packs</strong> use those fo=
undations and adapters to deliver user-facing intelligence.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3669de54dd96">
<p local-id=3D"c4f9ebd89e48"><strong>Runtime products</strong> determine ho=
w Bitloops is executed and consumed.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"14d053dd6057">
<p local-id=3D"9616cb5e3e51"><strong>Commercial / governance packs</strong>=
 add enterprise value, policy, trust, and paid product boundaries.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"ade125e605f5">This means, for example:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"d588258ce1ee">
<li local-id=3D"4302bb11e5a3">
<p local-id=3D"2da64674db88">a Knowledge pack may use a Confluence connecto=
r adapter</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c9622a7d197b">
<p local-id=3D"5f40459bf110">a Semantic Clones pack may use a specific embe=
dding provider adapter</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"161a7adb1718">
<p local-id=3D"fefb36c52e7d">a remote server runtime may host several capab=
ility packs and adapters under stricter security policy</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"06a5550fdb59">
<p local-id=3D"1617f9594d47">an enterprise governance pack may enforce poli=
cy over the shared runtime</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"e90ee3fff75c">
<h2 local-id=3D"fc24a80d01f5" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-WhyThisArchitectureIsNeededNow">Why This Arch=
itecture Is Needed Now</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9989b7dc4a83">This architecture is needed now because Bitloo=
ps is at the transition point where postponing these boundaries will make f=
uture growth more expensive.</p>
<p local-id=3D"08586d4a048a">Specifically, without it Bitloops risks:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"e503c4c55b72">
<li local-id=3D"31af57694cd5">
<p local-id=3D"ad6d75a82fb5">hardcoded agent support scattered through the =
product</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"83adc825bf23">
<p local-id=3D"ac998cedb616">language support becoming fragmented and dupli=
cated</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"45877be8c7dc">
<p local-id=3D"9befb336a571">server/runtime concerns leaking into local CLI=
 code paths</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"004fcd64cc49">
<p local-id=3D"01577c766a43">enterprise/security features arriving as one-o=
ffs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8733776c1910">
<p local-id=3D"03657b595c6f">poor packaging boundaries for paid product sur=
faces</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9050e35fc6c5">
<p local-id=3D"af0c6bcc1021">repeated host churn whenever a new ecosystem i=
ntegration is added</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b7139f7f4e7f">This is exactly the stage where a layered mode=
l creates leverage.</p>
<p local-id=3D"db0a43f21fc6">Too early and it would be overdesign.</p>
<p local-id=3D"8b2796a3f8e5">Too late and it becomes a costly retrofit.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"90c1c593675e">
<h2 local-id=3D"8739b17c640e" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-RecommendedNext-StepDocuments">Recommended Ne=
xt-Step Documents</h2>
<p local-id=3D"e8838936e257">This document is the umbrella note.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c98b1617d738">The next documents should deep dive into each =
category separately.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"9858188f2561" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-1.CapabilityPacks">1. Capability Packs</h3>
<p local-id=3D"9a6bd9edb4f5">Proposed deep-dive topics:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3fcbe7f38740">
<li local-id=3D"f5255319c3b3">
<p local-id=3D"a052521af122">contract shape</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"68736910caa4">
<p local-id=3D"662f0907a5b1">lifecycle and registration</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"af853f33f02a">
<p local-id=3D"900c0d2ab229">storage/provenance boundaries</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"36fa100a0363">
<p local-id=3D"787cb7f91984">examples: Knowledge, Semantic Clones, Test Har=
ness</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1484432dd77c">
<p local-id=3D"5b8ce6650078">packaging implications</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"8c9f80cd3ec0" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-2.AdapterPlugins">2. Adapter Plugins</h3>
<p local-id=3D"cab131b181cf">Proposed deep-dive topics:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3eefab862c9d">
<li local-id=3D"9deb86d11a63">
<p local-id=3D"e252f51ed5e1">agent adapters</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d33167bbc261">
<p local-id=3D"6343d60b8ffa">language pack model</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6241a2c13938">
<p local-id=3D"7cd55a405b79">model provider interfaces</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ceb30aa50aaa">
<p local-id=3D"85f52a47e192">connector/provider contracts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"de99b8373d4f">
<p local-id=3D"e75385b0fd66">coverage/test adapters</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0c1ad7ba7500">
<p local-id=3D"ca6df836e167">validation and compatibility rules</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"c7d1640f6233" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-3.RuntimeProducts">3. Runtime Products</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6d4a2415576b">Proposed deep-dive topics:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"4a04e2cd5bec">
<li local-id=3D"6d070a2612af">
<p local-id=3D"4a717105b89e">shared open-core crate boundaries</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c0c82893e57f">
<p local-id=3D"fc46167a5f43">local CLI runtime vs remote server runtime</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"a9333a0fec94">
<p local-id=3D"233743427d0b">dashboard/API runtime</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a9f0da025fa4">
<p local-id=3D"85b3ca5a3782">security, tenancy, and shared DB design implic=
ations</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0fa08a1dba30">
<p local-id=3D"baac9b576328">what should and should not be shared across ru=
ntimes</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"2ec87099c309" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-4.Commercial/GovernancePacks">4. Commercial /=
 Governance Packs</h3>
<p local-id=3D"1bcd02736dd1">Proposed deep-dive topics:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"77305e074cba">
<li local-id=3D"696554fa9ca9">
<p local-id=3D"224368863969">private inference</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eb3b1761c242">
<p local-id=3D"0fd2927b8b5b">internal enterprise connectors</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f58664d16208">
<p local-id=3D"e0c0273ccb10">policy/compliance modules</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d79dae472c7b">
<p local-id=3D"7e66d6eeaa5c">governance, audit, and org controls</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"63c05a8d6f50">
<p local-id=3D"3b305d032cce">paid tier boundary implications</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"eb9b70be72bd">
<h2 local-id=3D"530cc9a24d50" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-Recommendation">Recommendation</h2>
<p local-id=3D"49a1b916f6e1">Bitloops should formally adopt a <strong>layer=
ed extension architecture</strong> with four categories:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"d411d82dfb62">
<li local-id=3D"c91580a4b432">
<p local-id=3D"b5622cb1ca3a">Capability Packs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"254beb09d849">
<p local-id=3D"431bd9251735">Adapter Plugins</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"479c7b4f21ee">
<p local-id=3D"cc6c81ef01be">Runtime Products</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cb27cdb3b9da">
<p local-id=3D"9c9dc37b9665">Commercial / Governance Packs</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"dc69d4f7d234">This should become the framing for future arch=
itecture decisions.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2bf493c194b7">The key architectural shift is:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"27aaacd1a352">
<p local-id=3D"f019aa4912f7">Bitloops should think neither in terms of a mo=
nolith CLI nor =E2=80=9Cone plugin system for everything.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"1cd1daf9f4a6">It should think in terms of:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"b389bfb5cdb9">
<p local-id=3D"05019dd5892d"><strong>multiple explicit extension seams, eac=
h with the right boundary, contract, and product role.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"6bcacd87ce5f">That is the architecture most likely to maximi=
se:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"e7ae80709cdc">
<li local-id=3D"6bdbb8f0ea2f">
<p local-id=3D"ac221467ec24">platform clarity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cb5864eba0ec">
<p local-id=3D"0c2647b0cdda">delivery velocity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1d1a269f0432">
<p local-id=3D"a9f2f2958314">product coherence</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"555e4873acf8">
<p local-id=3D"4f37e071cc6c">ecosystem reach</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eb3fae395429">
<p local-id=3D"a19081349fd9">enterprise adaptability</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"98de42303f57">
<p local-id=3D"941bad0b314a">long-term commercial success</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"5d1513455d5b">
<h2 local-id=3D"cccd34f0a1b2" id=3D"BitloopsLayeredExtensionArchitecture:Wh=
yItIsNeededandHowItShouldLook-DiscussionPrompts">Discussion Prompts</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"d265b1e49e97">
<li local-id=3D"1c3eaa4ce9b6">
<p local-id=3D"56c9a5c47915">Are we aligned that Bitloops now needs a broad=
er extension architecture, not only DevQL capability plugins?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"481161297c8c">
<p local-id=3D"1157bb7fab96">Is the four-layer model the right taxonomy?</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"630dec4c1aa9">
<p local-id=3D"79333c85e46a">Which category should Bitloops formalise first=
: Capability Packs, Adapter Plugins, Runtime Products, or Commercial / Gove=
rnance Packs?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a4561ab6f33">
<p local-id=3D"6a6a561e562a">Should the remote server be treated as a separ=
ate runtime/product built on shared open core rather than as a CLI extensio=
n?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"60339a620164">
<p local-id=3D"50c941b6a96b">Which adapter seam is most urgent to define fi=
rst: agent adapters or language packs?</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
------=_Part_40_267410222.1774266732008--
